Rep. James Moran released his list of <a href="http://moran.house.gov/appropriations_requests.shtml">appropriations requests</a> today. A quick review shows he's asking for nine earmarks for former clients of PMA Group, worth a total of $17.5 million.</p><p>
Here's the <a href="http://www.opensecrets.org/lobby/firmsum.php?lname=PMA+Group&amp;year=2008">list</a> of 2008 PMA Group clients from Open Secrets, and below are links to earmarks requests and dollar amounts.</p><p>
<a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/SurfaceElectronicWar.shtml">General Dynamics</a> $2,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/AIREM.shtml">DDL Omni Engineering LLC</a> $3,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/Highlander.shtml">ITT Corp</a> $2,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/IntegratedAnalysis.shtml">Dynamis</a> $2,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/JEOD.shtml">Mobilvox</a> $2,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/JWIDS.shtml">Rockwell Collins</a> $1,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/ParagonFreq.shtml">Argon ST</a> $3,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/Tripline.shtml">Artis</a> $1,000,000; <a href="http://moran.house.gov/list/press/va08_moran/morenews/EARSgunshot.shtml">Planning Systems Inc.</a> $1,500,000;
